radiographic_examinations.findings: The appendix is enlarged and hyperemic measuring up to 9 mm with minimal adjacent fat stranding, consistent with acute uncomplicated appendicitis. No evidence of pneumoperitoneum or focal fluid collections. Visualized lung fields are within normal limits. There is no evidence of pleural or pericardial effusion. The liver, pancreas, spleen, adrenal glands, kidneys, urinary bladder, and reproductive organs are unremarkable. There is no retroperitoneal or mesenteric lymphadenopathy. No evidence of worrisome osseous lesions or acute fracture.
